cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it uses bibliometric data from the Web of Science. It is also likely to belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it analyses the growth of science based on the number of publications and cited references. Additionally, it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it examines the growth of science across all disciplines. It may also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it uses advanced statistical techniques to analyse the data. Finally, it could belong to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as it analyses the growth of science over time.
